<item>
            <title>[PIG-2587] Compute LogicalPlan signature and store in job conf</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/PIG-2587</link>
                <project id="12310730" key="PIG">Pig</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;We&apos;d like to be able to uniquely identify a re-executed script (possibly with different inputs/outputs) by creating a signature of the &lt;tt&gt;LogicalPlan&lt;/tt&gt;. Here&apos;s the proposal:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ol&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Add a new method &lt;tt&gt;LogicalPlan.getSignature()&lt;/tt&gt; that returns a hash of its &lt;tt&gt;LogicalPlanPrinter&lt;/tt&gt; output.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;In &lt;tt&gt;PigServer.execute()&lt;/tt&gt; set the signature on the job conf after the LP is compiled, but before it&apos;s executed.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;


&lt;p&gt;(1) would allow an impl of &lt;tt&gt;PigProgressNotificationListener.setScriptPlan()&lt;/tt&gt; to save the LP signature with the script metadata. Upon subsequent runs (2) would allow an impl of &lt;tt&gt;PigReducerEstimator&lt;/tt&gt; (see &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/PIG-2574&quot; title=&quot;Make reducer estimator plugable&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;PIG-2574&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;PIG-2574&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;) to retrieve the current LP signature and fetch the historical data for the script. It could then use the previous run data to better estimate the number of reducers.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
